            "body": "**Where to spend a T3 Albanese session \u2014 and where NOT to.**\n\nAlbanese already **builds green** (only `sorry` warnings). Do not chase a global 0-sorry state; several sorries are blocked on other active roadmap cones.\n\n**Attack these (self-contained, no cross-project blocker):**\n\n- `Genus0BaseObjects/Points.lean:512` \u2014 `GeometricallyReduced (Gm kbar).hom` (\ud835\udd3e\u2098 geom. reduced).\n- `Genus0BaseObjects/BareScheme.lean:220` \u2014 \u2119\u00b9 geometrically irreducible.\n- `Genus0BaseObjects/GmScaling.lean` (770, 821, 941) \u2014 ring/`Fin` identities on the \ud835\udd3e\u2098-scaling.\n- `Albanese/CodimOneExtension.lean` (1348, 1630, 1698) \u2014 the codim-1 extension math (`ALB.codim1`).\n\n**Do NOT attempt (blocked \u2014 will waste the session):**\n\n- `Albanese/AlbaneseUP.lean` \u00d77 \u2014 every sorry descends from `bundle : Bundle C := sorry`, the Jacobian carrier that needs **A.3** (`AJC.pic0av`). Cannot close inside Albanese.\n- `Picard/FGAPicRepresentability.lean` \u00d72 \u2014 `\u27e8sorry\u27e9` `HasPicSharp`/`HasPicScheme` existence = **FGA representability** (`AJC.picrep`).\n- `RiemannRoch/WeilDivisor.lean:377` \u2014 waits on a Mathlib upstream PR.\n\n**Notes:**\n\n- **No \"port from AJC\" shortcut here** \u2014 the AJC copies carry the *same* sorries (`AlbaneseUP` byte-identical), and `Genus0BaseObjects/*` are Albanese-only.\n- LSP dies on full-`import Mathlib` files; iterate with `lake build <module>` and read the printed goal state.",
