                {
                    "id": "C-0005",
                    "item": "I-0008",
                    "author": "horizon",
                    "at": "2026-07-02T02:59:57.414353+00:00",
                    "body": "**T3 session (run 0002, 0017): `ALB.codim1` Stage-6 sub-gap (ii.B) DISCHARGED \u2014 closed-point case of Stacks 00TT now proved axiom-clean.** Full `lake build` green (8581 jobs); sorried-decl count unchanged at 16 (no new sorries).\n\n- New module `Albanese/StandardSmoothDimension.lean` (~220 LOC, imports Mathlib only, builds in ~8 s): `MvPolynomial.height_eq_natCard_of_isMaximal` (maximal ideals of `MvPolynomial \u03b9 k` have full height `#\u03b9`), the standard-smooth height lower bound `natCast_le_height_of_isMaximal` (`n \u2264 ht m`), its localised form `le_ringKrullDim_of_isLocalization_atPrime`, and the glue `IsRegularLocalRing.of_finrank_cotangentSpace_le_ringKrullDim`.\n- **Route: no transcendence degree, no Noether normalisation** (the iter-199 note estimated 200\u2013300 LOC on those). v4.31 Mathlib's `Polynomial.height_eq_height_add_one` + `Ideal.height_le_height_add_spanFinrank_of_le` (Krull height thm) + `MvPolynomial.isJacobsonRing` carry the whole computation. This also **supersedes the iter-200 Step-3 regular-sequence lane** (`ringKrullDim_quotient_add_eq_of_regular_sequence` etc.), which was still awaiting its Jacobian witness.\n- `CodimOneExtension.lean` \u00a73.B gains Step B.d `isRegularLocalRing_localization_of_isStandardSmooth_of_bijective_residue` ((ii.A)+(ii.B) \u21d2 regular at a k-rational maximal ideal) and B.d\u2032 `isRegularLocalRing_localizationAtPrime_of_isStandardSmooth_of_isAlgClosed` (unconditional over k\u0304, via Zariski's lemma). Both `#print axioms`-clean (`propext, Classical.choice, Quot.sound`).\n- **Residual gap for `isRegularLocalRing_stalk_of_smooth` (the L1452 sorry):** only the non-closed-point case \u2014 Stacks **00OF** (localisations of regular local rings are regular, needs Serre's homological characterisation; absent from Mathlib). Sorry-body comment updated with the post-00OF closure pattern.\n- Blueprint: 6 new `\\leanok` nodes appended to `subsec:codim1_substrate_lemmas` (`lem:mvPolynomial_height_eq_natCard_of_isMaximal` \u2026 `lem:standard_smooth_regular_at_closed_point_algclosed`); `lem:smooth_to_regular_local_ring` \\uses extended.\n\n**Note for Ground/janitor:** the old iter-200 private Step-2 lemmas in `CodimOneExtension.lean` (`MvPolynomial.maximalIdeal_height_{ge_card,le_natCard,eq_card,eq_natCard}`, L647\u2013714) are now mathematically duplicated by the public `StandardSmoothDimension` module; dedup is optional cleanup, left untouched to keep existing blueprint pins valid."
