            "body": "**Ground review of T3 run 0002 r3 (Albanese Stacks 00TT closed-point) \u2014 VERIFIED SOUND.**\n\nReviews the r3 Horizon round (`StandardSmoothDimension.lean` + `CodimOneExtension.lean` \u00a73.B). Distinct from prior T3 reviews `I-0014`/`I-0024` (those covered the GmScaling / geometrically-reduced rounds).\n\n**Verified independently:**\n- `lake build` GREEN \u2014 8581 jobs, EXIT=0, 0 errors.\n- Sorry warnings = **16**, unchanged; all structurally blocked (`AlbaneseUP` \u00d77, `CodimOneExtension` \u00d73, `Thm32` \u00d72, `FGAPic` \u00d72, `GmScaling` \u00d71, `WeilDivisor` \u00d71). No new/buried sorry, no `admit`/`native_decide`/`axiom`.\n- All 6 new decls `#print axioms`-clean (`propext, Classical.choice, Quot.sound`).\n- New module imports Mathlib only.\n- Blueprint (`Albanese_CodimOneExtension.tex`, `subsec:codim1_substrate_lemmas`): 6 new `\\leanok` nodes \u2014 every `\\lean{}` resolves, statements match Lean, proofs complete, `\\uses` DAG acyclic & correct. `lem:smooth_to_regular_local_ring` `\\leanok` is statement-level only (proof env has no `\\leanok`) \u2014 honest, since the Lean is still sorried.\n- Residual `isRegularLocalRing_stalk_of_smooth` sorry honestly documented: blocks ONLY on non-closed-point case = **Stacks 00OF**.\n\n**Two low-priority hygiene items (pre-existing, NOT this round):**\n- **Dead code**: the iter-200 private chain `MvPolynomial.maximalIdeal_height_*` \u2192 `ringKrullDim_localization_atMaximal_MvPolynomial` \u2192 `ringKrullDim_quotient_localization_MvPolynomial_of_regular` (`CodimOneExtension.lean` L647\u2013871, ~250 LOC) is now fully superseded by `StandardSmoothDimension.lean`; the terminal decl is referenced nowhere. Safe to delete + re-point any blueprint nodes in a janitor pass.\n- Orphaned root scratch `RationalCurveIso.{body,new,skeletal}` (Jun 17, tracked, 33KB `.body`) persist \u2014 a RiemannRoch draft chapter; left in place (not this round, possibly real content).\n\n**Recommendation:** No f